# ADR Quality

When creating or editing ADRs, follow `@docs/adr/README.md` and the local agent
instructions in `@docs/adr/AGENTS.md`.

Required ADR content:

- One durable decision.
- Status and exact date.
- Context and problem statement.
- Decision drivers.
- Considered options and rejected alternatives when trade-offs exist.
- Decision.
- Consequences, including downsides and follow-up work.
- Links to related ADRs and repo artifacts.
- Supersession notes when replacing a previous decision.

Do not treat routine implementation notes, temporary experiments, or already
covered choices as new ADRs. Put task plans in `docs/plans/` unless they are
directly part of the decision record.
